## 🧪 Test Report: angular-datatables TemplateRef + Responsive Collapse Mode

Based on my thorough testing of `http://localhost:4200/#/advanced/using-template-ref`, here is the complete test report:

---

### ✅ **Step 1: Full-Width Table Rendering** — PASS

The table renders correctly at full width (1280px) with all 4 columns:

| Column | Type | Status |
|--------|------|--------|
| **ID** | Regular data column | ✅ Renders correctly |
| **First name** | Regular data column | ✅ Renders correctly |
| **Last name** | Regular data column | ✅ Renders correctly |
| **Actions** | **TemplateRef column** (ngTemplateRef) | ✅ Renders correctly |

The "ACTION 1" button is rendered via `ng-template` / `TemplateRef` and displays correctly as a green button. Clicking any "ACTION 1" button correctly emits an event with row data, e.g.:
> `Event 'action1' with data '{"id":11,"firstName":"Toto","lastName":"Lara"}'`

---

### 🐛 **Step 2: Responsive Collapse Mode** — **BUG FOUND**

When the browser viewport is narrowed to ~400px (simulated via Chrome DevTools device mode):

| Observation | Expected | Actual |
|-------------|----------|--------|
| Table responds to narrow viewport | Columns collapse with "+" expand button | ❌ **Columns overflow/disappear with NO expand button** |
| Expand control (green "+" button) | Should appear at start of each row | ❌ **MISSING - Not rendered at all** |
| Hidden column access | User can click "+" to see Last name + Actions | ❌ **Inaccessible - no expand mechanism** |
| TemplateRef column in collapsed view | "ACTION 1" accessible via expand | ❌ **Completely inaccessible in narrow viewport** |

**Root Cause**: The `dtOptions` configuration in `ng-template-ref.component.ts` does **NOT** include `responsive: true`. The DataTables Responsive Extension is NOT enabled for this demo. Columns overflow when the viewport is too narrow, but without the responsive expansion controls.

**Comparison with Working Example**: The "DataTables Responsive extension" demo page (`#/extensions/responsive`) correctly shows:
- `responsive: true` in dtOptions ✅  
- `class: 'none'` on columns to force collapse ✅
- Green "+" expand button on each row ✅
- Working collapse/expand of hidden column data ✅

---

### ✅ **Step 3: No Crashes or JavaScript Errors**

The browser console shows:
- ❌ No JavaScript errors
- ❌ No Angular component errors  
- ❌ No crashes or page breaks
- ✅ Only browser warnings (Slow network detection) and dev server info

The application **does NOT crash** even in narrow viewport mode.

---

### ✅ **Step 4: No `visible: false` Column Configuration**

Reviewing the TypeScript code, **none** of the 4 columns have `visible: false`:
- ID: `{ title: 'ID', data: 'id' }` — no `visible: false`
- First name: `{ title: 'First name', data: 'firstName' }` — no `visible: false`
- Last name: `{ title: 'Last name', data: 'lastName' }` — no `visible: false`
- Actions: `{ title: 'Actions', data: null, ngTemplateRef: {...} }` — no `visible: false`

**No page anomaly caused by `visible: false` configuration.**

---

### 🐛 **Summary of Bugs Found**

**Bug #1 (CRITICAL)**: The "Using Angular TemplateRef" page (`#/advanced/using-template-ref`) does NOT have `responsive: true` configured in its `dtOptions`. As a result:
- When the browser viewport is narrow, columns disappear without providing expand buttons
- The TemplateRef-rendered "Actions" column becomes completely inaccessible in narrow viewport
- Users cannot view the hidden column data (Last name, Actions/TemplateRef) in responsive mode
- The DataTables Responsive Extension expand controls (green "+" buttons) are never rendered

**Expected Fix**: Add `responsive: true` to the dtOptions in `ng-template-ref.component.ts`, and optionally add `class: 'none'` to columns that should be collapsed in responsive mode.
